            <entry xml:id="entry_kʼæsær" xml:lang="os">
                <form type="lemma"><orth>kʼæsær</orth></form>
                <sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                        <q>порог</q>
                    </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                        <q>doorstep</q>
                    </abv:tr></sense>
                <abv:exampleGrp>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>tæxūdy nyr wæ kʼæsæræj k˳y bazarin æz dær</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>о, если бы и мне запеть с вашего порога</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>Oh, if only I could also sing from your doorstep</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Коста"
                            /><biblScope>110</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>kæj koj kænaj — kʼæsærmæ<note type="comment" xml:lang="ru"> (д. %ike
                                koj kænaj — kʼæsærmæ%i)</note><note type="comment" xml:lang="en">
                                (Digor %ike koj kænaj — kʼæsærmæ%i)</note></quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>кого упомянешь — на пороге</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>whom you mention — he is at your doorstep</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <note type="comment" xml:lang="ru"> (поговорка: „легок на помине“)</note>
                        <note type="comment" xml:lang="en"> (saying: “to talk of the devil (and he
                            is sure to appear)”)</note>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_ЮОПам."/><biblScope>III
                            211</biblScope></bibl>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Gurdž._Æduli"
                            /><biblScope>92</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                </abv:exampleGrp>
                <etym xml:lang="ru">Вряд ли производное от <ref type="xr" target="#entry_kʼæs"/>
                    ‘хижина’: формант %i-ær%i не известен. Более вероятной кажется связь с
                        <mentioned xml:lang="ka" dialect="ka-x-rach"><lang/>
                        <w>kʼarseli</w>
                        <gloss><q>передняя</q></gloss></mentioned> (<bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_Беридзе"/><biblScope>20</biblScope></bibl>), ср. <mentioned
                        xml:lang="ka" dialect="ka-x-rach"><lang/>
                        <w>k’arse</w>
                        <gloss><q>порог</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ka"
                        dialect="ka-x-rach"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>косяк</q></gloss></mentioned> („%izgurbli da cʼqirtli%i“:
                            <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Саба"
                        /><biblScope>163</biblScope></bibl>). Звуковое развитие: %ik’arseli%i →
                    %i*kʼælsær%i → %ikʼæsær%i, как %ič’arxala%i → %i*cælxæra%i → <ref type="xr"
                        target="#entry_cæxæra"/> ‘свекла’.</etym>
                <etym xml:lang="en">It is hardly a derivative from <ref type="xr"
                        target="#entry_kʼæs"/> ‘hut’: a formant %i-ær%i is unknown. The more
                    probable relation is with <mentioned xml:lang="ka" dialect="ka-x-rach"><lang/>
                        <w>kʼarseli</w>
                        <gloss><q>entrance-room</q></gloss></mentioned> (<bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_Беридзе"/><biblScope>20</biblScope></bibl>), cf. <mentioned
                        xml:lang="ka" dialect="ka-x-rach"><lang/>
                        <w>k’arse</w>
                        <gloss><q>doorstep</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ka"
                        dialect="ka-x-rach"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>jamb</q></gloss></mentioned> („%izgurbli da cʼqirtli%i“:
                            <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Саба"
                        /><biblScope>163</biblScope></bibl>). The sound evolution: %ik’arseli%i →
                    %i*kʼælsær%i → %ikʼæsær%i, as in %ič’arxala%i → %i*cælxæra%i → <ref type="xr"
                        target="#entry_cæxæra"/> ‘beetroot’.</etym>
                <note type="internal">ужасный сорс</note>
            </entry>
